ext":"This class was written using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollLayout"},{"text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"duration"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It can support any language that the font supports."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use "},{"code":"LiveText","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance instead)."}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"UltraliteSDK","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","abstract":[{"text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses.","type":"text"}]},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller/scrolled(done:)":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"scrolled(done:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/scrolled(done:)","abstract":[{"text":"delegate callback.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/scrolled(done:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"scrolled","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"done"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"title":"ScrollLayout","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScrollLayout"}]}}}